  }, "Directory")), mdx("p", null, "This is a special type of a file in Unix, which only contains a list of other files (the contents of a directory). You don't work with directories directly, instead you manage them with standard commands provided with your OS. The whole directory structure of your Unix system is made of such special files with directory content in each of them.\nIn long-format output of ls, this type of file is specified by the \"d\" symbol:"), mdx("p", null, "$ ls -ld *\n-rw-r--r-- 1 greys greys1024 Mar 29 06:31 text\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 greys greys4096 Aug 21 11:00 mydir\n3.  ", mdx("strong", {
