l process running in your OS.\nHere's how the different types of special device files look in your ls output:"), mdx("p", null, "$ ls -al /dev/loop0 /dev/ttys0\nbrw-rw---- 1 root disk 7, 0 Sep 7 05:03 /dev/loop0\ncrw-rw-rw- 1 root tty 3, 48 Sep 7 05:04 /dev/ttys0\n4.  ", mdx("strong", {
